# Downloaded local-model artifacts (faster-whisper cache, Piper voice
# models, etc.) -- runtime data, not source. See app/config.py
# (PIPER_DOWNLOAD_DIR) and README.md for the offline/local fallback path.
models/

# User-tunable model parameter overrides (Model Lab) -- runtime-local state,
# not source. See app/model_settings.py.
model_settings.json

# Model Provider settings (which provider/model serves each capability) --
# runtime-local state, not source. See app/model_providers.py.
model_providers.json

# User-defined model presets (named field-value bundles) -- runtime-local state,
# not source. See app/model_presets.py.
model_presets.json

# Personal research notes that may contain pasted API keys -- never commit.
docs/refs/

# Raw exploratory call/session logs (e.g. from probing a vendor's own demo
# product) can contain live bearer tokens and aren't referenced by any code
# -- unlike the curated manifest/system-prompt docs alongside them, which
# ARE referenced (see app/model_adapters/manifest.py, app/pipeline.py) and
# stay tracked. Keep the log on disk, just never commit it.
docs/cartesia/voice-call-log.md

# Repo-root scratch TTS output only -- anchored so it doesn't shadow
# legitimately-committed same-named assets elsewhere (e.g.
# docs/minimax/voice-capability-*/assets/output.mp3, a capability sample).
/output.mp3
tests/
